Shrink Volume & Create New Partition in Windows
1️⃣ Open Disk Management
Press Windows + R.

Type:
diskmgmt.msc
Press Enter.

2️⃣ Shrink C: Drive
In Disk Management, find C: Drive.

Right-click on C: Drive.

Select Shrink Volume.

Enter the amount to shrink (e.g., 10 GB or desired size).

Click Shrink.

This will create an Unallocated Partition.

3️⃣ Create New Simple Volume
Right-click on the Unallocated space.

Select New Simple Volume.

4️⃣ New Simple Volume Wizard
Next through the wizard.

Assign a Drive Letter (e.g., D, E).

Click Next.

5️⃣ Format New Partition
Choose File System: Select NTFS.

Leave other options default.

Click Next.

6️⃣ Finish
A confirmation window will appear.

Click Finish.

